* PRACTICE 1:
* A furniture manufacturer in Yalova produces four different items: bookcases, desks, chairs, and bedframes.
* For each item required metal, wood and labor are given in Table 1.
* The company has only 225 hours of labor, 117 units of metal, and 420 units of wood available per day.
* Formulate an LP model that determines the production quantities that maximize (daily) net profit.
* Table 1 â€“ Resource requirements per unit (Given in the problem):
*                 Metal(unit)    Wood(unit)     Labor(unit)     Profit ($)
*     Bookcase        1              4              3             19
*     Desk            1              3              2             13
*     Chair           1              3              1             12
*     Bedframe        1              3              2             17

* MODEL 1:

SET i ITEMS /bookcase, desk, chair, bedframe/
    j COMPONENTS /metal, wood, labor/;

PARAMETER p(i) profit for each item /bookcase 19, desk 13, chair 12, bedframe 17/
          m(j) constraints for these components /metal 117, wood 420, labor 225/;
          
TABLE c(i,j) necessary components for each item
            metal wood labor
bookcase     1     4     3   
desk         1     3     2
chair        1     3     1
bedframe     1     3     2 ;

VARIABLE Z total profit;
POSITIVE VARIABLE x(i);

EQUATIONS
     ONJECTIVE
     CONSTRAINT;

OBJECTIVE..
Z =e= SUM(i, x(i)*p(i));

CONSTRAINT(j)..
SUM(i, x(i)*c(i,j)) =l= m(j);

MODEL question1 /all/ ;
SOLVE question1 USING LP MAXIMIZING Z;
